subsingleton:
#print MulActionWithZero.subsingleton /-
-- these fields are copied from `smul_with_zero`, as `extends` behaves poorly
-- see Note [lower instance priority]
protected theorem MulActionWithZero.subsingleton [MulActionWithZero R M] [subsingleton R] : subsingleton M :=
  ⟨fun x y => by rw [← one_smul R x, ← one_smul R y, subsingleton.elim (1 : R) 0, zero_smul, zero_smul]⟩
#align mul_action_with_zero.subsingleton MulActionWithZero.subsingleton
-/
smul_inv₀:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
#print smul_inv₀ /-
theorem smul_inv₀ [SMulCommClass α β β] [IsScalarTower α β β] (c : α) (x : β) : («expr • » c x)⁻¹ = «expr • » c⁻¹ x⁻¹ :=
  by
  obtain rfl | hc := eq_or_ne c 0
  · simp only [inv_zero, zero_smul]
  obtain rfl | hx := eq_or_ne x 0
  · simp only [inv_zero, smul_zero]
  · refine' inv_eq_of_mul_eq_one_left _
    rw [smul_mul_smul, inv_mul_cancel hc, inv_mul_cancel hx, one_smul]
#align smul_inv₀ smul_inv₀
-/
smul_eq_zero_of_right:

#print smul_eq_zero_of_right /-
theorem smul_eq_zero_of_right (a : R) (h : b = 0) : «expr • » a b = 0 :=
  h.symm ▸ smul_zero a
#align smul_eq_zero_of_right smul_eq_zero_of_right

smul_eq_zero_of_left:

theorem smul_eq_zero_of_left (h : a = 0) (b : M) : «expr • » a b = 0 :=
  h.symm ▸ zero_smul _ b

nontrivial:
#print MulActionWithZero.nontrivial /-
protected theorem MulActionWithZero.nontrivial [MulActionWithZero R M] [Nontrivial M] : Nontrivial R :=
  (subsingleton_or_nontrivial R).resolve_left fun hR => not_subsingleton M <| MulActionWithZero.subsingleton R M
#align mul_action_with_zero.nontrivial MulActionWithZero.nontrivial
